@Comment:	MOT gives semantic rather than print clue for Christa. Chi is a pretty fluent reader , obviously reading word by word since pauses not always at clause boundaries. Mot's intonation sounds like she's pretty bored with the task , but that's not necessarily true. Chi misses words within a sentence (after that he left much (better)) that also indicate preoccupation with single words. Context notes say that Chi reads the words and rarely looks at the pictures
